---
description: Set up Husky + lint-staged + Prettier + typecheck/tests on commit (Bun-first). Use when adding pre-commit hooks, Husky, or lint-staged.
alwaysApply: false
---

## SETUP PRE-COMMIT — SCOPE
- Use when the user wants commit-time formatting, lint-staged, or Husky in the **current repo**.
- **Default package manager: Bun** (stack.mdc). Fall back if lockfiles indicate otherwise: `pnpm-lock.yaml` → pnpm, `yarn.lock` → yarn, `package-lock.json` → npm.

## WHAT TO INSTALL (devDependencies)
- `husky` `lint-staged` `prettier`

```bash
bun add -d husky lint-staged prettier
```

(Replace with `pnpm add -D`, `yarn add -D`, or `npm install -D` if not using Bun.)

## INITIALIZE HUSKY
```bash
bunx husky init
```
- Ensures `.husky/` exists and `package.json` has `"prepare": "husky"` (or equivalent).

## `.husky/pre-commit` (Husky v9+ — no shebang required)
```text
bunx lint-staged
bun run typecheck
bun test
```
- **Adapt**: use `pnpm exec` / `yarn` / `npx` if not Bun.
- **Omit** `typecheck` or `bun test` lines if `package.json` lacks those scripts; tell the user.

## `.lintstagedrc` (JSON)
```json
{
  "*": "prettier --ignore-unknown --write"
}
```

## `.prettierrc` (only if no Prettier config exists)
```json
{
  "useTabs": false,
  "tabWidth": 2,
  "printWidth": 80,
  "singleQuote": false,
  "trailingComma": "es5",
  "semi": true,
  "arrowParens": "always"
}
```

## VERIFY
- `.husky/pre-commit` exists (executable on Unix; Windows relies on Husky runner).
- `.lintstagedrc` exists; `prepare` script present.
- Run `bunx lint-staged` once (with staged files) as smoke test.

## COMMIT
- Suggested message: `chore: add pre-commit hooks (husky + lint-staged + prettier)`

## OPTIONAL GLOBS (project rules only)
- If this rule is copied to `<project>/.cursor/rules/`, you may add `globs: package.json` or `.husky/**` so it attaches when editing hook config.

## NOTES
- `prettier --ignore-unknown` skips unsupported files.
- Order: lint-staged first (fast, staged only), then full typecheck/tests per testing.mdc expectations.
